Undid revision 928158385 by [[Special:Contributions/Harmanprtjhj|Harmanprtjhj]] ([[User talk:Harmanprtjhj|talk]]) This version is wrong and without reference. Indo-Scythians reached India from north, not south.

Indo-Scythians entered India via Pamir route not from the south to Taxila. The previous version provides no reference and the route from north taken by Indo-Scythians has been proven by Ahmed Hassan Dani.

I've not added something of my own or my personal point of view. I've just cited authentic research material. Dardic is not an ethnicity but a linguistic term and modern research support this claim or idea.
